eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Histological or cytological confirmation of cancer
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Have histological or cytological confirmation of cancer.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Refractory/relapsed solid tumors
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Have refractory/relapsed solid tumors and have exhausted all treatments with proven clinical benefit.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Measurable disease
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Have measurable disease as defined by RECIST v1.1.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: ECOG performance status
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Have an Eastern Cooperative Oncology Group (ECOG) performance status of 0 or 1.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Life expectancy
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Have a life expectancy of at least 12 weeks.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Adequate organ function
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Have adequate organ function as defined by protocol-specified laboratory values.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Recovery from prior therapy toxicities
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Have resolution of all clinically significant toxic effects of prior cancer therapy to Grade ≤1 by the National Cancer Institute Common Terminology Criteria for Adverse Events (NCI CTCAE), Version 5.0.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Urinary protein requirement
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Have urinary protein ≤1+ on dipstick or routine urinalysis (UA). If urine dipstick or routine analysis indicates proteinuria ≥2+, a 24-hour urine for protein must demonstrate <1000 mg of protein in 24 hours to allow participation in the study.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Sex
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Male or female. Contraceptive use by men or women should be consistent with local regulations regarding the methods of contraception for those participating in clinical studies. Male participants are eligible to participate if they agree to refrain from donating sperm and either be abstinent from heterosexual or homosexual intercourse or agree to use a male condom and female partner use of an additional highly effective contraceptive method during the intervention period and for at least 84 days/12 weeks following completion of study drug administration. Female participants are eligible if not pregnant or breastfeeding, and either not a woman of childbearing potential (WOCBP) or is a WOCBP using a highly effective contraceptive method during the intervention period and for at least 84 days/12 weeks after the last dose of study intervention. A WOCBP must have a negative highly sensitive pregnancy test within 24 hours before the first dose of study intervention.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Informed Consent
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Capable of giving signed informed consent as described in Appendix 1 which includes compliance with the requirements and restrictions listed in the informed consent form (ICF) and in this protocol.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Uncontrolled hypertension
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Have uncontrolled hypertension defined as systolic blood pressure (BP) >150 mmHg or diastolic BP >90 mmHg despite standard medical management.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Significant bleeding disorders
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Have significant bleeding disorders or experienced Grade 3/4 GI bleeding within 3 months prior to enrollment.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Hepatic impairment
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Have hepatic impairment (such as severe liver cirrhosis Child-Pugh B [or worse], cirrhosis with a history of hepatic encephalopathy, clinically meaningful ascites requiring ongoing treatment with diuretics and/or paracentesis, or history of hepatorenal syndrome).

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Arterial thromboembolic events
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Have experienced any arterial thromboembolic events (ATEs), including but not limited to myocardial infarction, transient ischemic attack, cerebrovascular accident, or unstable angina, ≤6 months prior to randomization.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Congestive heart failure or cardiac arrhythmia
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: The participant has clinically relevant congestive heart failure (CHF; New York Heart Association [NYHA] Grade ≥2) or symptomatic or poorly controlled cardiac arrhythmia.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Serious concomitant systemic disorder
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Have a serious concomitant systemic disorder that, in the opinion of the investigator, would preclude participation in the study.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Active infection requiring systemic therapy
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Have active infection requiring systemic therapy (e.g., bacterial infection requiring intravenous antibiotics at time of initiating study treatment, systemic fungal infection, or detectable viral infection requiring systemic therapy).

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: HIV positive participants
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Human immunodeficiency virus (HIV) positive participants (HIV 1 and/or 2; screening not required) are excluded unless they are well controlled on highly active antiretroviral therapy with: a. No evidence of acquired immunodeficiency syndrome (AIDS)-defining opportunistic infections within the last 2 years, and b. CD4 count >350 cells/μl.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Chronic active hepatitis B or C
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Have chronic active hepatitis B or C virus infection (screening not required).

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Prior or second concurrent primary malignancies
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Have prior or second concurrent primary malignancies that, in the judgment of the investigator and the Lilly clinical research physician (CRP)/clinical research scientist (CRS), may affect the interpretation of results. Participants with carcinoma in situ of any origin and participants with prior malignancies who are in remission and whose likelihood of recurrence is very low (such as basal cell carcinoma), as judged by the Lilly CRP/CRS, are eligible for this study.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Symptomatic CNS malignancy or metastasis
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Have symptomatic central nervous system (CNS) malignancy or metastasis (screening not required). Participants with treated CNS metastases are eligible for this study if they are not currently receiving corticosteroids (exceeding 10 mg/day prednisone or equivalent) and/or anticonvulsants to treat CNS metastases, and their disease is asymptomatic and radiographically stable for at least 30 days.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: History of GI perforation and/or fistula
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Have a history of GI perforation and/or fistula within 6 months prior to enrollment.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Serious or non-healing wound, ulcer, or bone fracture
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Serious or non-healing wound, ulcer, or bone fracture within 4 weeks prior to enrollment.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Chronic therapy with NSAIDs or antiplatelet agents
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Are receiving chronic therapy with nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory agents (e.g., indomethacin, naproxen, or similar agents) or other antiplatelet agents (e.g., clopidogrel or dipyridamole) within 7 days prior to first dose of study treatment. Aspirin use at doses up to 325 mg/day is permitted (see Section 10.6, Appendix 6).

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Prior treatment with IV ramucirumab
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Participants with prior treatment with IV ramucirumab as monotherapy or in combination with chemotherapy or targeted/biological agents on or outside of a clinical trial.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Recent participation in clinical study with investigational product
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Have participated, within the last 30 days, in a clinical study involving an investigational product. If the previous investigational product has a long half-life, 5 half-lives or 30 days (whichever is longer) should have passed. Exceptions will be considered on a case by case basis by the sponsor CRP/CRS.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Tattoos or scars over abdomen interfering with injection site assessments
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Have tattoos or scars over the abdomen, or other factors (e.g., rash, excessive folds of skin) that, in the investigator's opinion, would interfere with injection site assessments.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Elective or planned major surgery
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Have an elective or a planned major surgery during the course of the trial, or have undergone major surgery within 28 days prior to enrollment. Note: Central venous access device placement must occur at least 7 days prior to enrollment. Note: If participant received major surgery, the participant must have recovered adequately from the toxicity and/or complications from the intervention prior to starting therapy.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Major blood vessel invasion or encasement by cancer (NSCLC)
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Have radiologically documented evidence of major blood vessel invasion or encasement by cancer.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Intratumor cavitation (NSCLC)
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Have radiographic evidence of intratumor cavitation, regardless of tumor histology.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: History of gross hemoptysis (NSCLC)
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Have a history of gross hemoptysis (defined as bright red blood or ≥1/2 teaspoon) within 2 months prior to enrollment.
